data_answer:
I think about 344 out of 400 students are going to attend the talent show this year, which is 86% of the school. I figured it out by solving the problem ''What is 86% of 400?''.

 

 

                                                              A/B = P/100

 

                                Now you substitue the letters for the numbers.

                              

                                B = 400 (how many students attend the school.)

                                     

                                        P = percentage (in this case, 86%)

                                           

                                            And than you cross multiply.

                                                     

                                                     86%*400 = 34400

                               

          After that step you divide 34400/100 because percent means ''out of 100.''

                          

                                               Then you get your answer.

 

                                                               344

data_answer: I expect 340 students to show up or 85%. This number is based on the number of students who showed up, on the 2008 - 2009 chart above. To get this number I took the average of the chart (also known as mean) which was 85%. Then I took the median and got 84.5%. Well since these numbers are close together I rounded to a hole number 85%, the reason I did not round to 84% is, there is a .5, (anything that is or above .5 you round up, anything below .5 you round down.) Also the average was 85%. To get the number of students you have to cross multiply. To do that you have to turn the numbers into fractions, 85% = 85/100 because 85% just means 85 out of 100. Then you take your 400 and turn that into a fraction X/400, X is the number 85% represents. Now you go 100 * X to get 100X, then go 85 * 400 to get 34000. Now you get why we call it cross multiply :-). Then you put them side by side like this 100X=34000, you want to get X by its self so you have to take the 100 away, to do that you divide by 100 which leaves you with 1X. You don't really need the one so if you want you can get rid of it to be left with X. Well what you do to one side you do the other so you divide 34000 by 100 to get 340. Now if you had been flowing me on paper and you lined it up right you would have got X=340. Since X was you answer and it equals 340, 340 is your answer. That's how I got my answer.
